place.desc: St. Vincent's Well, now known as St. Vincent's Spring, is located about two miles from Bristol city centre on the north side of the river Avon in Clifton. The hot spring water flows from St. Vincent's rocks and drinking it was seen to be medically restorative. -----------
St Mungo’s Well was a popular cold water spring and bath at Copgrove, near Ripon, Yorkshire. It now seems to be covered by a paved area in front of Well House Farm (private land).

place.desc: Hipswell Hall was Alice Wandesford’s jointure property. It is a 15th-century manor house, built for the Fulthorpe family, whose coat of arms is carved on the bay window to the right. The estate passed to the Wandesfords of Kirklington and over the front door is a plaque dated 1596 with the initials of George Wandesford.

place.desc: East Newton Hall was the Thornton family home. William and Alice Thornton have it built anew after their marriage. They move here in 1662 and Robert Thornton was born here. It, together with Laistrop, was part of Alice Thornton’s jointure and she died here in 1707.
